div.div:
Audio
The Audio tab provides access to the user to configure the audio device used as input for the shader. Here, the user can set the device driver, sample rate, and number of channels.
There will also be a real-time meter showing the volume of the input signal and a spectral analysis, allowing the user to visualize the frequencies and magnitude.
